{{!
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  This adds the Inklings tab content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/templates/components/profile-custom.hbs
  LOCATION: Inside the tab-content <div>

  STEP 1: Locate the file
  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/templates/components/profile-custom.hbs
  2. Find the <div> with class="tab-content" (usually after the profile tab list)

  STEP 2: Find the insertion point
  3. Inside that tab-content <div>, look for any existing <div class="tab-pane">
  4. You'll paste your code AFTER the last tab-pane div (but still INSIDE the tab-content)

  STEP 3: Copy and paste
  5. Copy the <div> block below (between the markers)
  6. Paste it inside the tab-content div, at the end (before the closing </div>)
  7. Save the file

  IMPORTANT DETAILS:

  ID MATCHING:
  - The id="inklings-tab-pane" below MUST match the href="#inklings-tab-pane"
    in profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs
  - Do NOT change this value

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - The component uses: characterId, viewerId, and isStaff
  - These are passed from: this.char.id, this.viewer.id, and this.viewer.isStaff
  - If your profile-custom.hbs uses different property names, update them here
  - Common alternatives: character instead of char, user instead of viewer, etc.
  - Check the rest of your profile-custom.hbs to see what names are used

  ABOUT THE COMPONENT:
  The inklings-tab component is self-contained - it handles all Inkling operations:
  - View existing Inklings
  - Create new ones
  - Add messages and rolls
  - Submit for staff review
  - Share with other characters/groups
  - All changes save immediately (doesn't use the profile page's save flow)
}}

  {{! ---START COPY HERE--- }}
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="inklings-tab-pane">
    {{inklings-tab characterId=this.char.id viewerId=this.viewer.id isStaff=this.viewer.isStaff}}
  </div>
  {{! ---END COPY--- }}
